ity range spanned in the considered\nobservations lies between ~2x10^32 and ~1x10^34 erg/s. All this allows us to\nsuggest a scenario consisting of a wide binary system in which a neutron star\naccretes matter from the wind of an M giant.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Nov 2001 14:08:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
